stylometry: Some advantages of simulation models is they allow you to see how sensitive the system is to change it. Simulation models also allow you to look at a whole distribution, rather than just an answer. You would use simulation in a management or business situation to try to change certain variables and see if it affects the outcome. For example, you can run a simulation on how many servers you need at a restaurant. Simulation lets you test more than one answer at a time, so you can test 8 servers, 10 servers, 12 servers, etc. and compare the @Risk information to choose the best answer.
